      "agent_id": "spark-reviewer",
      "created_at": "2026-05-26T17:53:42.748956+00:00",
      "result_id": "res_767cb1ce803f",
      "status": "success",
      "summary": "Reviewed commit b695843 and added findings for Route B strict-typing/auditability risks to `.team/artifacts/findings-spark-reviewer-2.2.3-slice-2.md`. Commit: `4a32a9f`.",
      "task_id": "msg_200edf218f64"
    },
    {
      "agent_id": "realistic-tester",
      "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:00:06.448908+00:00",
      "result_id": "res_0cd890d340b8",
      "status": "partial",
      "summary": "Slice 2 Stage 7 attempt 8 ran from scratch on candidate b695843. SC_C, SC_A env/spec, S1-S4, SC_B, SC_D, and CHECK_A all passed. The runner halted in S5, but post-halt evidence classifies this as a harness/test-design bug, not a product bug: worker_a-d were interacted and resumed; worker_e/f were never interacted, had no session_id, emitted restart.resume_decision decision=fresh_start, and fresh-spawned, which matches the b695843 Route B contract. The private runner still asserts 6/6 restart_mode=resumed, which is stale. S6 and CHECK_B idle CPU were not executed after the halt. One real subscription E2E run was used; remote workspace/evidence retained for diagnosis.",
      "task_id": "msg_250df27201f7"
    },
    {
      "agent_id": "realistic-tester",
      "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:07:40.695938+00:00",
      "result_id": "res_00bea0635507",
      "status": "success",
      "summary": "Slice 2 Stage 7 PASS on b695843. I patched the private harness S5 detector from stale 6/6-resumed semantics to Route B: interacted+session => resumed, never-interacted+no-session => fresh_start, and any restart.atomic_refusal fails. Forward-resume used the existing real S5 restart evidence, then ran S6 and CHECK-B. Final verdict is PASS / Product behavior passed / complete. S5 Route B rows: worker_a-d decision=resume restart_mode=resumed; worker_e/f decision=fresh_start restart_mode=fresh. S6 remove-agent cleanup ok. CHECK-B active avg CPU 4.013% (<20), idle avg CPU 3.700% (<5).",
      "task_id": "msg_84fcafb01ffa"
    },
    {
      "agent_id": "claude-runtime-developer",
      "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:25:41.818790+00:00",
      "result_id": "res_c5732189e663",
      "status": "success",
      "summary": "CI hotfix committed in 518303d.\n\nROOT CAUSE: tests/test_gap29_send_trust_prompt_integration.py hardcoded /private/tmp/teamA-slice2-env-slice-2-20260526T103705Z at lines 21, 40 (fixture strings) and 77, 181 (Path.mkdir). Linux CI has no /private/tmp/, so Path.mkdir raised FileNotFoundError before mocks could install. The Mac mini capture run had copied its real workspace path verbatim into the source.\n\nFIX SHAPE: four fixture constants → four *_TEMPLATE constants with a {WORKSPACE} placeholder. New _materialize_workspace_and_fixture(prompt_template) helper calls tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix=\"team-agent-gap29-trust-real-\"), resolves the path, and returns (workspace, prompt_template.replace(_WORKSPACE_PLACEHOLDER, str(workspace))). Each test method calls the helper at the top of its body and uses the returned tuple instead of constructing Path(\"/private/tmp/...\") manually. workspace-dir-match in attempt_trust_auto_answer still hits because the prompt's quoted directory equals the real on-disk Path. shutil.rmtree on teardown unchanged.\n\nTEST METHODS — 4 unittest tests + 3 subTests = 6 distinct cases (matching the leader's \"6 测试\" count). All green:\n  test_leader_receiver_path_detects_trust_prompt_answers_then_re_pastes              ok\n  test_leader_receiver_path_detects_trust_prompt_with_blank_tail_then_re_pastes      ok\n  test_send_path_detects_real_codex_trust_prompt_answers_then_re_pastes              ok\n  test_send_path_detects_trust_prompt_variants_with_blank_tail_ansi_and_wrapping     ok\n    subTest blank_tail  ok\n    subTest ansi        ok\n    subTest wrapped     ok\n\nFULL SUITE: Ran 763 tests in 193.082s, FAILED (errors=1, skipped=5). Single remaining error is the pre-existing test_leader_double_ctrlc PermissionError on os.killpg under local sandbox — environmental, unrelated.\n\nConfirmed `grep -n \"/private/tmp/teamA\" tests/test_gap29_send_trust_prompt_integration.py` returns zero hits. Single focused commit, only the failing file touched. Linux CI should now find a real tempdir on every run instead of failing on a non-existent /private/tmp/.\n\nNext: leader handles tag deletion + re-tag + re-push.",
      "task_id": "msg_a0f4ab5fd0a6"
    },
    {
      "agent_id": "constitution-reviewer",
      "created_at": "2026-05-27T07:24:25.703366+00:00",
      "result_id": "res_302e8385f805",
      "status": "success",
      "summary": "Gap 39 Leader-Ownership Unified Lease — design verdict: APPROVE-WITH-CONSTRAINTS (C1–C22 + ruling C23). The identity-keyed acquire-on-vacant lease is the correct §1.7 (transport ephemeral / identity persistent) and §1.2 (thick infra) architecture — today's bug exists precisely because pane_id leaked into identity; the lease fixes that and removes the manual takeover dance. It is infra-tier mutex+owner_epoch, NOT a forbidden MUST-NOT-4 workflow state machine. All risk is in the edges → discrete testable constraints, none warrant rejection.\n\nFull verdict body delivered to leader-inbox.log fallback (send hit leader_pane_missing — the Gap 39 symptom itself) for materialization at .team/artifacts/slice-0.2.4-1-cr-design-verdict.md (msg_21c81f8b1653).\n\nBLOCKING-SAFETY CORE (must land): C4 (no-confirm acquire only on unambiguous-dead pane-absent/PID-gone; ambiguous signals require --confirm — prevents stealing a live owner) · C5 (acquire binds caller pane only if leader-shaped+same-host+same-user+cwd-in-workspace; a plain-shell `send` never binds itself) · C17 (owner+receiver written to BOTH state files under one runtime_lock — kills today's takeover-writes-workspace-only divergence) · C20/C21 (every acquire/rebind/epoch-advance AND every refusal emits a structured audit event — the Gap 32/38 silent-mutation anti-pattern).\n\nPer-axis: A→C1-C4 (live-OS probe not cached pid; process-TREE not current_command; TOCTOU re-validate-in-lock via epoch CAS). B→C5-C6 (single-os-user trust boundary). C→C7-C10 (realpath both sides; subtree containment; cwd is a SUPERSET filter, team resolved by --team or broadcast; env fast-path retained). D→C11-C14 (converge 3 verbs to ONE code path, claim-leader canonical; derive identity from pane; vacant=no-confirm / live=--confirm / holder=idempotent; operator-facing not agent CLI). E→C15-C16 (T1 acquire + T2 broadcast share ONE epoch CAS; broadcast only at ≥2 candidates, else silent — §1.6 preserved). F→C17-C19 (atomic dual-write; post-write equality invariant; doctor heals divergence + stale receiver). G→C20-C22 (closed reason enum + redacted uuid + old/new pane). H→C23 ruling: coordinator.pid false-negative is a SEPARATE gap, queue it (agrees with slice OUT); decoupled from Gap 39 provided C1 holds.\n\nTest gaps to ADD beyond §39 cheap-gate surface: T8 false-positive-dead (busy/cd'd live leader not stolen), T9 TOCTOU race, T10 dual-state atomicity, T11 non-leader caller refusal, T12 realpath/symlink. Realistic-tester external validation REQUIRED: Mac mini one-shot must reproduce the verbatim 2026-05-27 substrate (user-launched no-UUID-env claude pane + dead recorded owner + restart → one-shot delivery + both files agree + audit events + live-owner guard + branch-window broadcast).",
      "task_id": "msg_a42af4e873d2"
    }
  ],
